Method Detail

onCardDetailsSubmitted

void onCardDetailsSubmitted(CardDetails details,
                            boolean addToTouch,
                            java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> encryptedCardDetails)
Called with newly-added card details once validated and encrypted.

encryptedCardDetails always contains the same card details, encrypted against client-side encryption key supplied to the client.

When addToTouch is True, encryptedCardDetails will contain an additional key VTNewCardViewController.KEY_VENMO_SESSION_TOKEN, containing the encrypted Venmo Touch session token.

In exceptional circumstances, the Venmo Touch session token may not be available. In such cases, VTNewCardViewController.KEY_VENMO_SESSION_TOKEN will be reported as the empty string.

Parameters:
details - the cleartext card details
addToTouch - true if the user requested adding the card to Venmo Touch
encryptedCardDetails - the card details, along with the additional key VTNewCardViewController.KEY_VENMO_SESSION_TOKEN, all encrypted with the client-side encryption key
